@fruitoftheloom and @wildlifetailor have rethought the humble pack tee with a simple premise: one T-shirt fit can't do everything. Landing July 4, the collaboration arrives in two distinct two-packs, each containing one white and one black tee, with buyers choosing between a wide silhouette designed to be worn on its own and a slimmer cut built specifically for layering under shirts and tailoring.⁠
⁠
Rather than forcing a single fit to cover every use case, the collaboration splits the functions across two purpose-built body types. It's WILD LIFE TAILOR's vision of the ultimate pack tee, treating the category as a design problem worth solving rather than a commodity, with sizes running from S to XL across both fits.⁠

